        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Published_EnergyDeviationReport",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate a report on energy consumption deviations for a specified billing period and agency. It compares current energy consumption data with data from the same period in the previous year, calculating the percentage deviation. The procedure logs its execution for auditing purposes and filters results to include only those with a deviation of 25% or more."
        }
      ]
    },
